  <bioghist id="aspace_bcc341a3492a83329aab2c9ab1ed92a2">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>tatiana de la tierra was one of the founders and editors of the Latina lesbian magazines, <title>Esto No Tienne Nombre</title> and <title>Conmocion</title>. Her writings have appeared in periodicals and anthologies since 1987. In 2002, she published the book <title>For The Hard Ones: A Lesbian Phenomenology</title>.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_d3ebfeda5573a46017c1de681055eb20">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Self-published collections of her writings, copies of published articles and chapters, some of her unpublished pieces, and a collection of flyers and posters, mostly on Latina lesbian themes.</p>  </scopecontent>
